{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782271631206,"sessionID":"ses_108557056ffeZ4F0zj9y2EiqOH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_48hiuryq","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"gh api repos/GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular/pulls/64/comments --jq '.[] | {id, path, line, body, user: .user.login, created_at}'","description":"Fetch line-level review comments"},"output":"{\"body\":\"[HIGH] `approve_pr()` always submits reviews with `--comment` regardless of the agent's `Overall Assessment`.\\n\\nThe agent produces `APPROVE / REQUEST_CHANGES / COMMENT` in the `Overall Assessment` line, but this is never parsed. Every review is posted as a neutral comment, defeating the severity-based workflow.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395290,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] After filtering comments against the diff, the number of skipped comments is logged but not surfaced to the user during the interactive prompt.\\n\\nIf all inline comments are skipped, the user gets a \\\"Review submitted!\\\" message with zero visible inline comments. Show a clear warning.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395292,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] Config values are not validated.\\n\\n`interval_seconds` could be 0 or negative. `timeout_seconds` could exceed `interval_seconds`. Add basic validation.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395295,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] `subprocess.run([editor, draft_file], check=False)` won't handle editor commands with arguments (e.g. `code --wait` or `vim -R`).\\n\\nUse `shlex.split(editor) + [draft_file]`. Same issue with `pager` a few lines below.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395298,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[HIGH] `cmd.split()` breaks on spaces in paths (e.g. worktree paths with spaces).\\n\\nThis will cause git worktree commands to fail silently or with confusing errors. Use `shlex.split()` instead.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395299,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[LOW] File uses JSON format but has a `.conf` extension.\\n\\nConvention mismatch — `.conf` typically implies INI/key-value format. Consider renaming to `pr-review.json` or using TOML/INI.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395300,\"line\":1,\"path\":\"pr-review.conf\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[HIGH] Inline comments posted via `gh api repos/{repo}/pulls/{num}/comments` — creates standalone PR comments, not review comments.\\n\\nThey won't be threaded under the review event. Should use the `repos/{repo}/pulls/{num}/reviews` endpoint with a `comments` payload to create proper review comments associated with the review.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395306,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[HIGH] Hardcoded to 1 PR per cycle.\\n\\n`reviewed += 1` followed by `break` exits the loop after the first successful review, leaving remaining pending PRs untouched until the next 10-minute poll. README calls this \\\"PoC mode\\\".\\n\\nRemove the `break` and add concurrency control (e.g. `max_parallel_reviews` config) or at minimum review all pending PRs sequentially in one cycle.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395307,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] The regex for extracting inline comments is fragile.\\n\\nIt won't match comments that deviate slightly (extra spaces, missing colon, different dash styles). Consider using a markdown parser or simpler line-by-line parsing.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395308,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] Parser uses `add_help=False` and only adds `--help`. The `-h` shortcut is not registered, so `python pr-review.py -h` falls into `remaining` and triggers `die(\\\"Unknown option: -h\\\")`.\\n\\nAdd `\\\"-h\\\"` to the `--help` argument or use `add_help=True`.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395311,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] No timeout on git fetch/worktree/add/checkout operations.\\n\\nA hung remote or stale lockfile will block the poller indefinitely. Add a timeout parameter to the git subprocess calls.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395315,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] File contains hardcoded model (`ollama-cloud/glm-5`) and repo (`GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular`).\\n\\nIf this config contains API keys or tokens in the future, it could be accidentally committed. Consider adding `pr-review.conf` to `.gitignore` and shipping a `pr-review.conf.example` instead.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395316,\"line\":1,\"path\":\"pr-review.conf\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[HIGH] `subprocess.run(cmd, shell=True, ...)` executes `conf.notify` through the shell with string substitution.\\n\\nEven though it's config-driven, `shell=True` is unnecessary and dangerous if the config is ever templated from untrusted input. Use `shlex.split()` and `shell=False`.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395317,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] `signal_handler` calls `sys.exit(0)` without writing pending state changes.\\n\\nIf the user interrupts during a `set_pr_state` call or while a draft is being written, state is lost. Should flush state before exiting.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395319,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] `$schema` points to `https://opencode.ai/config.json` — an external URL dependency.\\n\\nIf opencode.ai is unreachable or changes the schema, validation fails. Consider vendoring or documenting this dependency.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395321,\"line\":1,\"path\":\"opencode.json\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[LOW] Mixed Indonesian (\\\"Script buat auto-review PR...\\\") and English.\\n\\nPick one language for professional consistency.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395322,\"line\":1,\"path\":\"scripts/README.md\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[LOW] Agent permissions and description are duplicated between `opencode.json` and `.opencode/agents/pr-review.md`.\\n\\nSingle source of truth violation — they can drift.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:07Z\",\"id\":3401395329,\"line\":1,\"path\":\".opencode/agents/pr-review.md\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[HIGH] Monolithic 1305-line script — needs modular separation.\\n\\nAll logic (config, state, worktree, review, interactive UI, approval, revision) lives in one flat file. This makes testing, reading, and maintaining impossible.\\n\\nSuggested separation:\\n```\\npr_review/\\n  __init__.py\\n  config.py        # Config loading/validation\\n  state.py         # state_PR.json CRUD\\n  worktree.py      # Git worktree lifecycle\\n  review.py        # OpenCode spawning + output parsing\\n  submit.py        # GitHub review submission\\n  cli.py           # Interactive prompt + argparse\\n  daemon.py        # Main polling loop\\n```\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:07Z\",\"id\":3401395351,\"line\":1,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[LOW] State file is read/written on every get/set call. No in-memory caching.\\n\\nFor a poller that touches state frequently, this is inefficient.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:07Z\",\"id\":3401395355,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed in the refactor. Review submission now uses the parsed `### Overall Assessment` as the GitHub review `event`, so `APPROVE` / `REQUEST_CHANGES` / `COMMENT` are preserved instead of always posting a neutral comment.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:04Z\",\"id\":3411699277,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. The approval flow now shows the assessment, valid inline-comment count, skipped count, and every skip reason before submission, with explicit confirmation required when anything is skipped.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:06Z\",\"id\":3411699423,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. Config loading now validates types and enforces `interval_seconds \\u003e 0`, `timeout_seconds \\u003e 0`, and `timeout_seconds \\u003c= interval_seconds`, with startup failing fast on invalid values.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:08Z\",\"id\":3411699575,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. Editor and pager commands are now parsed with `shlex.split()` before appending the draft path, so commands like `code --wait` and `vim -R` work correctly.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:10Z\",\"id\":3411699713,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. Internal command execution now uses argument lists throughout, and user-provided command strings are only split at the configuration boundary with `shlex.split()`, so spaces in paths no longer break worktree/git commands.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:12Z\",\"id\":3411699872,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed with the latest cleanup. The committed JSON-in-`.conf` file has been removed; the runtime now uses ignored local `pr-review.json` plus the committed `pr-review.json.example` documented in the README.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:14Z\",\"id\":3411700008,\"line\":1,\"path\":\"pr-review.conf\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. Body, assessment, commit SHA, and inline comments are now submitted together in one `POST /pulls/{number}/reviews` request, so the inline comments belong to the same GitHub review event.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:15Z\",\"id\":3411700148,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. The poller no longer stops after the first successful review; it processes all pending eligible PRs in the cycle with a bounded worker pool via `ThreadPoolExecutor`.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:17Z\",\"id\":3411700331,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. Parsing is now section-aware and line-oriented, with explicit validation plus tests for separator/whitespace variants and malformed inline-comment lines.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:19Z\",\"id\":3411700497,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. CLI parsing now uses the default `argparse` help handling, so both `-h` and `--help` work, with a regression test covering `-h`.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:22Z\",\"id\":3411700652,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. GitHub and git/worktree subprocess calls now run with explicit timeouts so a hung fetch/worktree operation cannot block the poller indefinitely.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:23Z\",\"id\":3411700772,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\"body\":\"[HIGH] `approve_pr()` always submits reviews with `--comment` regardless of the agent's `Overall Assessment`.\\n\\nThe agent produces `APPROVE / REQUEST_CHANGES / COMMENT` in the `Overall Assessment` line, but this is never parsed. Every review is posted as a neutral comment, defeating the severity-based workflow.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395290,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] After filtering comments against the diff, the number of skipped comments is logged but not surfaced to the user during the interactive prompt.\\n\\nIf all inline comments are skipped, the user gets a \\\"Review submitted!\\\" message with zero visible inline comments. Show a clear warning.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395292,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] Config values are not validated.\\n\\n`interval_seconds` could be 0 or negative. `timeout_seconds` could exceed `interval_seconds`. Add basic validation.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395295,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] `subprocess.run([editor, draft_file], check=False)` won't handle editor commands with arguments (e.g. `code --wait` or `vim -R`).\\n\\nUse `shlex.split(editor) + [draft_file]`. Same issue with `pager` a few lines below.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395298,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[HIGH] `cmd.split()` breaks on spaces in paths (e.g. worktree paths with spaces).\\n\\nThis will cause git worktree commands to fail silently or with confusing errors. Use `shlex.split()` instead.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395299,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[LOW] File uses JSON format but has a `.conf` extension.\\n\\nConvention mismatch — `.conf` typically implies INI/key-value format. Consider renaming to `pr-review.json` or using TOML/INI.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395300,\"line\":1,\"path\":\"pr-review.conf\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[HIGH] Inline comments posted via `gh api repos/{repo}/pulls/{num}/comments` — creates standalone PR comments, not review comments.\\n\\nThey won't be threaded under the review event. Should use the `repos/{repo}/pulls/{num}/reviews` endpoint with a `comments` payload to create proper review comments associated with the review.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395306,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[HIGH] Hardcoded to 1 PR per cycle.\\n\\n`reviewed += 1` followed by `break` exits the loop after the first successful review, leaving remaining pending PRs untouched until the next 10-minute poll. README calls this \\\"PoC mode\\\".\\n\\nRemove the `break` and add concurrency control (e.g. `max_parallel_reviews` config) or at minimum review all pending PRs sequentially in one cycle.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395307,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] The regex for extracting inline comments is fragile.\\n\\nIt won't match comments that deviate slightly (extra spaces, missing colon, different dash styles). Consider using a markdown parser or simpler line-by-line parsing.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395308,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] Parser uses `add_help=False` and only adds `--help`. The `-h` shortcut is not registered, so `python pr-review.py -h` falls into `remaining` and triggers `die(\\\"Unknown option: -h\\\")`.\\n\\nAdd `\\\"-h\\\"` to the `--help` argument or use `add_help=True`.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395311,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] No timeout on git fetch/worktree/add/checkout operations.\\n\\nA hung remote or stale lockfile will block the poller indefinitely. Add a timeout parameter to the git subprocess calls.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395315,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] File contains hardcoded model (`ollama-cloud/glm-5`) and repo (`GDP-ADMIN/gl-tabular`).\\n\\nIf this config contains API keys or tokens in the future, it could be accidentally committed. Consider adding `pr-review.conf` to `.gitignore` and shipping a `pr-review.conf.example` instead.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395316,\"line\":1,\"path\":\"pr-review.conf\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[HIGH] `subprocess.run(cmd, shell=True, ...)` executes `conf.notify` through the shell with string substitution.\\n\\nEven though it's config-driven, `shell=True` is unnecessary and dangerous if the config is ever templated from untrusted input. Use `shlex.split()` and `shell=False`.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395317,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] `signal_handler` calls `sys.exit(0)` without writing pending state changes.\\n\\nIf the user interrupts during a `set_pr_state` call or while a draft is being written, state is lost. Should flush state before exiting.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395319,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[MEDIUM] `$schema` points to `https://opencode.ai/config.json` — an external URL dependency.\\n\\nIf opencode.ai is unreachable or changes the schema, validation fails. Consider vendoring or documenting this dependency.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395321,\"line\":1,\"path\":\"opencode.json\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[LOW] Mixed Indonesian (\\\"Script buat auto-review PR...\\\") and English.\\n\\nPick one language for professional consistency.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:06Z\",\"id\":3401395322,\"line\":1,\"path\":\"scripts/README.md\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[LOW] Agent permissions and description are duplicated between `opencode.json` and `.opencode/agents/pr-review.md`.\\n\\nSingle source of truth violation — they can drift.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:07Z\",\"id\":3401395329,\"line\":1,\"path\":\".opencode/agents/pr-review.md\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[HIGH] Monolithic 1305-line script — needs modular separation.\\n\\nAll logic (config, state, worktree, review, interactive UI, approval, revision) lives in one flat file. This makes testing, reading, and maintaining impossible.\\n\\nSuggested separation:\\n```\\npr_review/\\n  __init__.py\\n  config.py        # Config loading/validation\\n  state.py         # state_PR.json CRUD\\n  worktree.py      # Git worktree lifecycle\\n  review.py        # OpenCode spawning + output parsing\\n  submit.py        # GitHub review submission\\n  cli.py           # Interactive prompt + argparse\\n  daemon.py        # Main polling loop\\n```\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:07Z\",\"id\":3401395351,\"line\":1,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"[LOW] State file is read/written on every get/set call. No in-memory caching.\\n\\nFor a poller that touches state frequently, this is inefficient.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-12T07:10:07Z\",\"id\":3401395355,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"david-gdp\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed in the refactor. Review submission now uses the parsed `### Overall Assessment` as the GitHub review `event`, so `APPROVE` / `REQUEST_CHANGES` / `COMMENT` are preserved instead of always posting a neutral comment.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:04Z\",\"id\":3411699277,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. The approval flow now shows the assessment, valid inline-comment count, skipped count, and every skip reason before submission, with explicit confirmation required when anything is skipped.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:06Z\",\"id\":3411699423,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. Config loading now validates types and enforces `interval_seconds \\u003e 0`, `timeout_seconds \\u003e 0`, and `timeout_seconds \\u003c= interval_seconds`, with startup failing fast on invalid values.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:08Z\",\"id\":3411699575,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. Editor and pager commands are now parsed with `shlex.split()` before appending the draft path, so commands like `code --wait` and `vim -R` work correctly.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:10Z\",\"id\":3411699713,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. Internal command execution now uses argument lists throughout, and user-provided command strings are only split at the configuration boundary with `shlex.split()`, so spaces in paths no longer break worktree/git commands.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:12Z\",\"id\":3411699872,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed with the latest cleanup. The committed JSON-in-`.conf` file has been removed; the runtime now uses ignored local `pr-review.json` plus the committed `pr-review.json.example` documented in the README.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:14Z\",\"id\":3411700008,\"line\":1,\"path\":\"pr-review.conf\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. Body, assessment, commit SHA, and inline comments are now submitted together in one `POST /pulls/{number}/reviews` request, so the inline comments belong to the same GitHub review event.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:15Z\",\"id\":3411700148,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. The poller no longer stops after the first successful review; it processes all pending eligible PRs in the cycle with a bounded worker pool via `ThreadPoolExecutor`.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:17Z\",\"id\":3411700331,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. Parsing is now section-aware and line-oriented, with explicit validation plus tests for separator/whitespace variants and malformed inline-comment lines.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:19Z\",\"id\":3411700497,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. CLI parsing now uses the default `argparse` help handling, so both `-h` and `--help` work, with a regression test covering `-h`.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:22Z\",\"id\":3411700652,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n{\"body\":\"Addressed. GitHub and git/worktree subprocess calls now run with explicit timeouts so a hung fetch/worktree operation cannot block the poller indefinitely.\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-15T07:30:23Z\",\"id\":3411700772,\"line\":null,\"path\":\"scripts/pr-review.py\",\"user\":\"josephgreffenkomala\"}\n","exit":0,"description":"Fetch line-level review comments","truncated":false},"title":"Fetch line-level review comments","time":{"start":1782271631191,"end":1782271631200}},"id":"prt_ef7aad73e001FQXjTCKTpgWiu6","sessionID":"ses_108557056ffeZ4F0zj9y2EiqOH","messageID":"msg_ef7aac8580010NT4SvImYW5ddA"}}
